From: Paulo Alcantara <pc@manguebit.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Apr 2024 16:34:04 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] smb: client: fix potential UAF in
 cifs_signal_cifsd_for_reconnect()
Git-commit: e0e50401cc3921c9eaf1b0e667db174519ea939f
References: bsc#1224766, CVE-2024-35861
Patch-mainline: v6.9-rc3

Skip sessions that are being teared down (status == SES_EXITING) to
avoid UAF.

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Paulo Alcantara (Red Hat) <pc@manguebit.com>
Signed-off-by: Steve French <stfrench@microsoft.com>
Acked-by: Enzo Matsumiya <ematsumiya@suse.de>
---
 fs/cifs/connect.c |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

--- a/fs/cifs/connect.c
+++ b/fs/cifs/connect.c
@@ -206,6 +206,10 @@ cifs_mark_tcp_ses_conns_for_reconnect(st
 		spin_unlock(&ses->chan_lock);
 
 		spin_lock(&ses->ses_lock);
+		if (ses->ses_status == SES_EXITING) {
+			spin_unlock(&ses->ses_lock);
+			continue;
+		}
 		ses->ses_status = SES_NEED_RECON;
 		spin_unlock(&ses->ses_lock);
 
